def: Water tinctured with roses by distillation.
To make odious or hateful. [Obs.] South.
Making chilly or cold; depressing; discouraging; cold; distant;as, a chilling breeze; a chilling manner.-- Chill"ing"ly, adv.
Having the right of presentation, or offering a clergyman tothe bishop for institution; as, advowsons are presentative,collative, or donative. Blackstone.
A kind of tobacco for smoking, made of the dried leaves,coarsely broken; -- so called from the rush baskets in which it ispacked in South America. McElrath.
A unit of electromotive force equal to one thousand volts.
A net for catching crabs. Halliwell.
A cloth used for washing dishes.
Dropsy of the subcutaneous cellular tissue; an effusion ofserum into the cellular substance, occasioning a soft, pale,inelastic swelling of the skin.
Containing reproof; reprehensive; as, reprehensory complaint.Johnson.
